                            <comment id="15352925" author="erans" created="Tue, 28 Jun 2016 12:44:46 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks for the update.&lt;br/&gt;
Sorry I hadn&apos;t looked further, but I find it confusing that the patch refers to &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/MATH-296&quot; title=&quot;LoessInterpolator.smooth() not working correctly&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;MATH-296&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;MATH-296&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; (in comments and method names), rather than this report.&lt;br/&gt;
It&apos;s fine to use the same test case but the issue being different, a code reviewer should be directed to here.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15353080" author="rwaj" created="Tue, 28 Jun 2016 14:33:45 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Is there a convention for or against using issue ids in test method names?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15353133" author="erans" created="Tue, 28 Jun 2016 14:57:09 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;It is fine to use an issue id, but the id should be the proper one: this report is &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/MATH-1379&quot; title=&quot;LoessInterpolator can update bandwidth interval incorrectly&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;MATH-1379&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;MATH-1379&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; so a related test method would be &lt;tt&gt;testMath1379&lt;/tt&gt;, not &lt;tt&gt;testMath296&lt;/tt&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Note however that test methods are better named according to what they are supposed to check, without necessarily referring to a JIRA report.&lt;br/&gt;
The latter is used as a last resort.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;For example, this gives full information (what is checked, and that the unit resulted from a JIRA report):&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;    &lt;span class=&quot;code-comment&quot;&gt;// Cf. MATH-1379
&lt;/span&gt;    @Test
    &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;public&lt;/span&gt; void testUpdateBandwidthIntervalWithUnevenXSpacing() {
      &lt;span class=&quot;code-comment&quot;&gt;// ...
&lt;/span&gt;    }
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17383448" author="erans" created="Mon, 19 Jul 2021 16:47:28 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Patch file was outdated but fix has been applied and (Java) unit tests have been added in commit 8968416790a42eebd5583718800ccc4fe55c8cbc (&quot;master&quot; branch).&lt;br/&gt;
Thanks.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
